SIMPLE: squint-eyed
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Squint-eyed
<hw>Squint"-eyed`</hw> <pr>(-⟦imac⟧d`)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having eyes that squint; having eyes with axes not coincident;
cross-eyed; also called <altname>squinty-eyed</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Looking obliquely, or asquint; malignant; <as>as,
<ex>squint-eyed</ex> praise; <ex>squint-eyed</ex>
jealousy</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squintifego</ent>⟦br⟧
